OL,3,CWarmest May and spring on record in
OL,4,CUK, Met Office figures show
OL,6,FAnd, alongside other records broken,
OL,7,Fit was also the wettest UK spring
OL,8,Fsince 1986 and the sixth wettest on
OL,9,Frecord. An average 301.7mm of rain
OL,10,Ffell on the country across March,
OL,11,FApril and May, nearly a third (32%)
OL,12,Fmore than usual for the season.
OL,14,FThe wettest spring on record was in
OL,15,F1979, when the UK experienced an
OL,16,Faverage 327.0mm of rain.
